{
  "texts": [
    "This study also detailedly explored the strengths and weaknesses of CSL strategy and approaches, equipping researchers with crucial insights and recommendations to make informed decisions.",
    "In addition, a comparative analysis was conducted on a selection of relevant works, allowing for a deeper understanding of the performance and characteristics of different CSL techniques.",
    "For datasets, a total of 196 datasets were identified from the selected papers.",
    "The common practice of using multiple datasets enabled the assessment of model generalizability and facilitated a more comprehensive evaluation of cost-sensitive methods.",
    "The findings additionally showed that MIT-BIH Arrhythmia emerged as the most frequently used dataset, owing to the numerous selected studies in cardiology and its recognition as a reputable benchmark dataset."
  ]
}